Friday 3/13/15: Stereographic projection and rotations of the sphere. Warmup: 1-dimensional case. Rotation of the circle corresponds to a linear fractional transformation (LFT) f(t)=(at+b)/(ct+d) of the extended line RU{&infin;} under stereographic projection. Review of LFT's (see also Stillwell p.104).
