Wednesday 1/28/15: The spherical cosine rule. Review of cosine rule in R<sup>2</sup>. Review of spherical coordinates from 233. For a spherical triangle ABC on a sphere of radius 1 with angles a,b,c and opposite side lengths &alpha;, &beta;, &gamma; we have cos(&alpha;)=cos(&beta;)cos(&gamma;)+sin(&beta;)sin(&gamma;)cos(a).
<br>
