Wednesday 4/17/13. Computation of the hyperbolic distance in the Poincare disc model D: The hyperbolic length of a curve in D parametrized by F:[a,b] -> D, F(t)=(u(t),v(t)) is given by the integral of (2 sqrt(u'(t)<sup>2</sup>+v'(t)<sup>2</sup>)/(1-u<sup>2</sup>-v<sup>2</sup>))dt from a to b. In particular, it follows that a rotation R with center the origin defines a hyperbolic isometry of the disc D. Discussion of the corresponding hyperbolic isometry of the upper half plane H.
